//
1. Use create react app
2. Have node and npm installed; verify by checking version in VS Code terminal
3. Have LTS version
4. npx create-react-app <react-app-name>
5. yarn is mainly packaged with react app, but many prefer npm
6. #4 becomes npx create-react-app <react-app-name> --use-npm
7. cd <react-app-name>, npm run start
